shoot:description:This gallery covers much of March, where I didn't come across a whole lot to photograph.  Highlights here include a Red-shafted Northern Flicker (the common subspecies here) excavating a cavity in a dead tree visible from our yard, a Yellow-shafted Northern Flicker (pretty rare here) chowing down on some berries at eye level, and a Hermit Thrush (which I hadn't seen all winter!).
